			<td width="100%"><span class="postbody">The guild is currently looking for more players to join us. Basically we want loyal people who can raid in EST prime time and want to enjoy the game. The Guild is currently raiding PoP Elemental Planes. We have been successful in killing Xegony and Fennin with Rathe and Corinav in our sights, which will flag the majority of the guild Plane of Time. Applicants to open classes should have or be working towards getting EP Flags. Questions concerning admissions may be directed to the recruitment contacts in game: Tudana or Linkagge 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Class Status </span>(May 12, 2004): 
<br />
Applications are <span style="color: yellow">currently open </span>for the following Classes: 
<br />
<span style="color: yellow">Berzerker 
<br />
Cleric 
<br />
Paladin
<br />
Shaman 
<br />
Warrior 
<br />
Wizard </span>
<br />

<br />
We are looking for players that are willing to give time for the continued progression of Eternal Sovereign. This means we want newer members that will be <span style="font-weight: bold">logging in 4 times a week or more from 7pm to 12am EST.</span> 
<br />

<br />
Applications from other classes may be considered, but gaining a prevote / vote for membership while in a closed class is much more difficult. 
<br />
*Positive Factors such as (1) EP flagged, (2) previous membership of allied guilds in good standing with ES, (3) Mixing well with current ES membership (4) showing full knowledge of class skills, are traits highly considered in applications for a close class. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: violet">Closed Classes:</span> as of 05-05-04
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><span style="color: violet">Bard:</span> (Lv65, EP flagged, 200+ AA`s, EN3, IM3, IIM, JF3, FM, SM3 and a min of 10 raids before prevote/vote)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Beastlord:</span>: (Lv65, EP flagged, 200+AAs, Run3, MGB, PoS, ND3, min 10 raids)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Druid:</span> (Lv65, EP flagged, AA`s –MGB,HG3,HA3,RC,SoTW3, min 10 raids, must mix with druid team)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Enchanter: </span>
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Magician:</span> (Lv65, EP Flagged, Run3, Regen3, MC1, SCM3, Pet Hold, SCS3, SCF3, FoM3, FoMM3, min 10 raids)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Monk:</span> (Lv65, EP Flagged, no EGO, Tier A raider, Run3, RF, CM)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Necro:</span> (closed is closed, no exceptions)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Ranger: </span>(lv65, EP flagged, 100+ AAs, AM3, EQ, Innate Camo, min 10 raids)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Rogue:</span> (Lv54, EP flagged, 200+ AAs SoS, Escape, Chaotic Stab, CF3, Ambidex, PE, PP5, min 10 raids)
<br />
<span style="color: violet">Shadowknight:</span> (Lv65, EP Flagged, 150+ AAs – SCF3, IHT, UT3, Run3,CA3, CS3, LR5, ID5, PE, ND3, PD5 min raids 10)</span>
<br />

<br />
If you want to talk in game <span style="text-decoration: underline">/join esrecruit:sexy </span>
<br />

<br />
Recruitment Contacts: <span style="font-weight: bold">Tudana, Linkagge </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Application Procedure - PLEASE READ BEFORE APPLYING</span>
<br />

<br />
Applicants please post in this forum once you have decided you would like to join Eternal Sovereign. After you have attended some raids, an officer will ask the guild to consider you for membership. When this vote happens is, in large part, up to you. If you feel you are ready to be considered, that is, you think you have proven yourself to be ES material, you can ask the recruitment officers to put you up for a vote. The recruitment officers may do so on their own as well. There is no set amount of time or raid attendance before you are considered by the membership. 
<br />

<br />
Consideration will take place in the closed voting forum. Members will have one week to discuss your application. If the guild votes for admission, you will be notified of acceptance and invited to join the guild. If the guild decides admission is not appropriate at that time, an officer will contact you in game. If at any time you decide to withdraw your application, please post that intent in this forum. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">All applicants </span>must post the following information. Copy/paste and fill in the info: </span>
<br />
Main character name: 
<br />
Class: 
<br />
Race: 
<br />
Level: 
<br />
AA's (do you have the ones most necessary for your class?): 
<br />
Time zone: 
<br />
Average play time per week: 
<br />
Alternate character names: 
<br />
Class: 
<br />
Level for any alts above level 40 (this includes any characters you share with others): 
<br />
Keys/Flags: 
<br />
Basic level of equipment and/or magelo profile: 
<br />
Listing of ALL previous guild memberships: 
<br />
Any other comments (this is the MOST important part please feel free to share anything about yourself here): 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Eternal Sovereign also employs a three week probationary period for new members. During this probationary period, you will not have voting rights and your involvement may be limited. Also during this probationary period, any actions on your part that are disruptive to the guild or tarnishing to the reputation of the guild will lead to your immediate removal. The rules for the probationary period may seem a bit harsh, but they are necessary to protect the guild and its members. Once the three weeks have passed, you will be accepted as a full member of the guild and be granted all the rights and privileges of membership in Eternal Sovereign. 
<br />

<br />
A few restrictions: 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Single Applications Only </span>- While we appreciate interest from groups of friends, each person will be individually considered. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Recruited Class </span>- You are being recruited based on the guild’s need for a particular class. You are expected to play that class as your main character, so apply with the character you intend/want to play. Applications with Other Guilds - While we understand you may be looking for the guild that best fits you and your play style, we will not consider your application to Eternal Sovereign if you have an open application with another guild. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Minimum Flag Requirements for open classes </span>- None at the moment. However, the suggested minimum flags are POJ Trial, BOT, Grummus, AD, TT and MB. The closer you are to meeting this, the less stressful your first few months in the guild will be. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Additional Remarks </span>
<br />

<br />
Meeting the level and class restrictions are not the only requirements for admission. You will be evaluated by the membership based on your performance and demeanor during raids. During voting, members are asked to give greater weight to how you would fit into the group dynamic, far more so than class, level or benefit to the guild. ES is one of the oldest guilds on the server. The majority of members have been friends for a long time and the friendships come first. How you will affect the stability and atmosphere within the guild is a primary concern. 
<br />

<br />
ES is not a power gamers` guild. Raids are not mandatory and we try to maintain a casual atmosphere. Our primary goal is guild advancement, that is we are trying to progress as far into the endgame as possible without losing the friendly atmosphere that has defined ES over the last two years. Unfortunately, there are some considerations that have to be made to continue guild advancement in the endgame. So, if you choose to be a strictly casual player, these considerations will have an impact on you. 
<br />

<br />
We qualify loot based on attendance. If you want to loot items that have significant impact on your character and guild ability, you will be expected to participate in raids and other activities. Very nice items will still be available for the casual player. But, the higher the investment into a player, the higher the return the guild expects to receive. Please ask an officer for an explanation of our loot system if you have questions about this. 
<br />

<br />
If you are interested in joining, there are a few things you need to know. Raids are dependent on who is available on any given night. If we don’t have the people to kill mob X; we may look for another target or just decide to let everyone go experience. Generally we try to maintain as little pressure to raid as possible. That’s not to say we don’t raid. Most weeks will see at least five nights of raiding, but there may be weeks we only raid once or twice. We may also choose to end raid nights early if it’s getting late and we don’t have the interest to pursue anything else. Most of our members have significant real life commitments and raids just depend on who has time on any given night. 
<br />

<br />
Bear in mind too, there is no set timetable for new encounters. We have certain goals and continually work to improve every member of the guild with gear and endgame experience. But, when we attempt a given encounter is completely up to the raid leaders. Many of our encounters are based on luck, as the casual play style does not allow us to jump on mobs the second they spawn. This play style can be frustrating if you are a powergamer who would prefer raids every night and new loot clogging your bags. We accept the limitations, but we do not let them hinder our progress. We have chosen a long, slow and steady course for the guild. If you would like to join us, you need to both understand and accept the path we have chosen.</span></td>
		</tr>
